Cell.Data: The modeling activities, either for the semi-formal model, or formal model, are supposed to be based on the Sub-System Requirement System, according to the Open ETCS Software LifeCycle. As this document is not yet issued, this modeling activity is based on the Subset026 so far. Shouldn't we consider other inputs for modeling (Subset035 for instance)?

The current modelling activity related to D2.5 is for benchmarking of the different modelling approaches, not the complete model. Therefore I think your question is out of scope for this document.
Regarding the "big model" that should start after tool choice, Sylvain Baro made clear that the SSRS are going to be based on Subset-026 plus any additionally needed document.

In the introduction, the scope of the document is defined to be related to a Formal Model. The requirements presented in this document can be used for both formal and semi-formal models.
Maybe a sentence could be added in the introduction, explaining that this tool benchmarking is valuable for all modelling activities, and not only for the Formal Model Activities (that would be described in the D2.3 and D2.4 documents).

It is right. I have not updated this document after the safety workshop in Paris which have seen the concept of SSRS (and also Semi-Formal) really begin.
Sentence added in the introduction : "This benchmarking is valuable for all modelling activities (including semi formal and formal)."

Maybe a precise list of the points that have to be fulfilled by each kind of model (semi-formal, formal, Model Based Testing, Safety Analysis...) would be valuable (The Tool Artifacts Matrix refined for each kind of model for instance)

I don’t agree with this point. It is not in D2.5 scope. In D2.5, i give only the content of the modelling / proof activities. I give a sort of « tool box » for modelling, with different means of description. Each candidate who wants to benchmark his method/tool has to indicate himself what he is able to model and prove, in WP7.

I don’t think property PROPERTY_3.5.3_01 is correct. Indeed, in some situations, the OBU is allowed to have two com. Sessions established at the same time, Be it for an RBC-RBC handover (see 3.15.1.3.1 of S026 v3.3.0), or for two concurrent RIU connections (see 3.9.3.6b of S026 v3.3.0)

Yes, it is true. The actual property is relevant if there is only one modem in the train. So, i propose to let the property as it is, but with a sentence which precises that it is done in the context of only one modem in order to avoid ambiguities.
"and taking the assumption that the OBU is fitted with only one modem for this benchmarking"

The required property should be under the responsibility of chapter 3.5 “Management of radio communication”, or more precisely: it should be specified within 3.5.
For property PROPERTY_3.5.3_01 this is not the case; it should be replaced by a property that reflects a function specified in 3.5 directly like “3.5.3.4 The onboard shall establish a communication session if ordered from trackside”.

I don’t understand why the actual property is not relevant to chapter 3.5. It is written in 3.5.2 and the content of 3.5 is about connection and disconnection.
The property you propose can not be used since to be checked, a property must be alway true, or always false. It is not the case for your example.

according to § 3.5.2.1 stating that each ‘entity’ describing a GSM-R/ LTE unit (Modem) shall only exchange data with one other ‘entity’ meaning RBC.
In the case you have only one GMS-R entity onboard, the requirement ‘PROPERTY_3.5.3_01 is correct, not so if you have two GSM-R entities onboard as part of the OBU.
I would propose the following formulation:
PROPERTY_3.5.3_01 ‘Each of the maximum two radio communication entities of the’ OBU shall never have two different communication sessions established at the same time (with the same RBC or with two different)

Yes, it is true. The actual property is relevant if there is only one modem in the train. So, i propose to let the property as it is, but with a sentence which precises that it is done in the context of only one modem in order to avoid ambiguities.
"and taking the assumption that the OBU is fitted with only one modem for this benchmarking"

From V&V point of view the data structure is very important. there should be at least one message modeled with high priority since the exchange on message level should couple the modeling tool with verification tool for black box testing.
The priorities have been discussed before. It is too late to change them.

The Property "PROPERTY_4.6.2_02 OBU shall never leave Isolated mode (no transition from Isolation is specified)" has got exceptions in 4.4.3.1.3. Maybe adding a 'without proven thath this is a safe operation' could add additional confidence.

To leave the IS mode, it require a special operating procedure. It is outside the functionnality of the OBU itself. This procedure will not be modelled for this benchmark, so there is no problem to let this property as it is.

Property "PROPERTY_5.9_02 Brake command should always be triggered when an OS mode acknowledgement is requested and 5 seconds are elapsed" does have exceptions to it when e.g. a mode level is issued within the 5 seconds. Maybe using "PROPERTY_5.9_02 Brake command should always be triggered when an OS mode acknowledgement is not acknowledgef for 5 seconds."

The deliverable essentially lists a subset of requirements from the standard that shall be used for evaluating the candidate tools. This is a really helpful input. However, it does not contain any process or methodology for benchmarking as the title suggests. Thus, in my opinion it is an incomplete and not a final document and should either be extended, or the title should be changed to something like "A Subset of Requirements for Benchmarking of Tools" which is possibly a problem. The appendix is helpful but misses a short description of each variable.

Ok, the title will be changed as proposed.
Description of the variable are in the SRS.
The form of the common language defined in Appendix is not easy to use in practice.
The appendix is just a help, i can not do it better without doing huge useless copy/paste of the SRS.
